#Text=Veluwezoom National Park
#Text=Veluwezoom National Park
#Text=( Nationaal Park Veluwezoom ) is the oldest national park in the Netherlands .
#Text=It is in the province of Gelderland in the Netherlands .
#Text=Understand

#Text=Veluwezoom is only one of the several parts of the Veluwe , which consists of the National Parks of Veluwezoom and Hoge Veluwe , along with the other forested areas between the cities of Arnhem , Apeldoorn , Barneveld and Zwolle .
#Text=The Veluwe consists of 1100 km , whereas Veluwezoom consists of 50 km .
#Text=History
#Text=The Veluwezoom was consists of a complex terminal of posh moraines dating back to the Saalian glaciation ( ~150.000 years ago ) .
#Text=This resulted in the high contrast in height compared to the rest of the country .
#Text=Veluwezoom 's highest point is roughly 110 meters above sea level , whereas most of the Netherlands barely pokes above sea level .

#Text=When the appreciation of nature and landscapes started growing in the Netherlands ( ~1900 ) , many high class citizens of the cities , located mostly in the west , went on vacations in these areas .
#Text=Veluwezoom was one of these areas .
#Text=Many inns were built during this time to offer places to stay for the visiting tourists .
#Text=During the 20th century the area started to attract more visitors due to a continued rise in prosperity .
#Text=Landscape
#Text=The landscapes on Veluwezoom were formed during the two most recent glacial periods .
#Text=During the Saalian , the second most recent glacial period , the ground , mostly existing of sand , was formed into hills and ' mountains ' by the glaciers spanning over the north of Europe .
#Text=When these glaciers melted , many streams were formed , which , though they contain no water , can still be found in the park .

#Text=During the Weichselian glaciation , the most recent glacial period , the ice did n't reach the Netherlands , yet the ice just north of the country caused sand and dust to be blown into the country .
#Text=The sand and dust gathered in the valleys between the mountains , and formed a fertile layer of Loess in the south of the Veluwe .
#Text=The highest point of the park is Signaal Imbosch which stands at 109.9 metres .
#Text=Flora and fauna
#Text=The existing flora is mostly decided on by the former management of the park .

#Text=The area has a large amount of heathlands , on which you will find common heather ( Calluna ) , cross-leaved heath ( Erica tetralix ) , common gorse ( Ulex europaeus ) and common broom ( Cytisus coparius ) .
#Text=In the old forests of ' t Asselt and in the Onzalige Bossen you will find mostly brake growing underneath oak and birch trees .
#Text=On the sand dunes you will find mostly blueberries and lingonberries , which are edible .
#Text=Underneath the pine trees on the Eerbeeksche Veld you will find large amounts of wavy Hair-grass ( Deschampsia flexuosa ) .

#Text=In the forests and on the loess you will most likely find birch and oak trees , which are native to the area , along with Norway spruce , larch , Douglas fir and sweet chestnut trees , which occasionally grow over 40 meters tall .
#Text=In these forests you will most likely find no vegetation underneath the trees .
#Text=Lastly , in the valley of the Beekhuizense beek ( Beekhuizen stream ) you will find saxifrage .
#Text=On the most scanty areas of the Veluwe the vegetation can be damaged easily , which has caused very sandy areas to be created .
#Text=The only area on Veluwezoom where you will find this landscape is the rather small Rozendaalse Zand .
#Text=In 2009 17 hectares of forest were cut to give the wind more influence on the area .
#Text=The national park Veluwezoom has many big mammals such as the red deer , fallow deer , roe deer and wild boars .
#Text=It also houses predators such as foxes , badgers , ermines and pine martens .
#Text=The park has high numbers of birds , which are n't hard to come across .
#Text=Amongst these are the rather uncommon kingfishers , eurasian hobby 's , honey buzzards , ravens , nightjars , stonechats , skylarks and green and black woodpeckers .
#Text=During winters you will find great grey shrikes as well .
#Text=Out of the seven reptiles that are native to the Netherlands , six can be found in Park Veluwezoom .
#Text=These six are the European adder , smooth snake , grass snake , slow worm , sand lizard and viviparous lizard .
#Text=Get in
#Text=The best way to enter the park is from the south side .
#Text=The official visitors centre is located near the village of Rheden .
#Text=The visitors centre can be reached by using the A12 in the direction of Arnhem .
#Text=When you find yourself on the roundabout by the river IJssel ( knooppunt Velperbroek , exit 27 ) , exit the A12 and turn onto the A348 in the direction of Rheden , Zutphen and Doesburg .
#Text=Use exit 2 ( Rheden ) to turn onto the Groenestraat .
#Text=When you have reached the end of the Groenestraat .
#Text=On the roundabout you find yourself on several parking spaces are indicated by signs .
#Text=Fees and permits
#Text=Entrance to the park is free , services however , can be arranged through the park 's website , which can be easily translated to English .
#Text=Get around
#Text=Cars are allowed on several indicated roads , yet a car wo n't get you far .
#Text=Your best option is to go biking or hiking in the park .
#Text=Camping is not allowed , so when travelling large distances through the park , going by bike is highly recommended .
#Text=Bikes can be rented at the visitors centre ( Heuvenseweg 5a , 6991 JE Rheden ) .
#Text=Routes are freely available online .
#Text=Camping
#Text=Camping in the park is not allowed .
#Text=Visit one of the hotels or campsites found by the edge of the park .
#Text=Accommodation is listed under Overnachten ( Accommodation ) on the park 's website .
#Text=Stay safe
#Text=Do not approach wild boar , since they can be aggressive towards humans when they have piglets .
